      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(googlechat): validate appPrincipal is required when audienceType is app-url",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen `audienceType` is `\"app-url\"`, the `appPrincipal` field (OAuth 2.0 client ID) is required for Google Chat add-on token validation. Previously, omitting `appPrincipal` in this mode would silently pass schema validation, leading to a confusing runtime failure.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Add `superRefine` validation to `GoogleChatConfigSchema` that rejects `app-url` configurations without `appPrincipal`\n- Propagate the same validation to per-account overrides (`accounts.*`)\n- Inherit parent `audienceType` for account-level validation when not explicitly overridden\n- Update JSDoc comments on `appPrincipal` to document the requirement\n- Update `docs/channels/googlechat.md` example and notes\n- Add regression tests covering:\n  - `app-url` with/without `appPrincipal`\n  - Empty/whitespace `appPrincipal`\n  - `project-number` without `appPrincipal` (still allowed)\n  - Account-level overrides with inherited parent `audienceType`\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm test src/config/config.googlechat-appprincipal.test.ts` — 8/8 passed\n- `pnpm test src/plugins/contracts/config-footprint-guardrails.test.ts` — 11/11 passed\n- `pnpm exec oxlint` — 0 warnings, 0 errors\n\n## Compatibility\n\n- No breaking change for existing valid configs\n- `project-number` audience type is unaffected\n",
